      %ol
        %li 
          %strong Eligibility: 
          The Contest is ONLY open to legal residents of Ontario who reside near the Greater Toronto Area and have reached the age of majority ("Participants"), except SCB-TO Executive Board members, Contest organizing committee members, and Contest judges.
        %li 
          %strong Contest period: 
          Participants may submit photos ("Entries") from 12:00 a.m., Eastern Time, April 14, 2014 to 11:59 p.m., Eastern Time May 14, 2014. Any Entry received outside of this period will be automatically disqualified. SCB-TO reserves the right to change any deadline(s) as the result of causes beyond its immediate control.
        %li 
          %strong To enter: 
          Participants must register, upload a digital copy of their photographs to www.scbtorontophotos.com and provide a high quality (300 dpi) 8x10" or 8x12" hard copy display print within the contest period. SCB-TO highly recommends Participants order, at their own expense, display prints from Downtown Camera (www.downtowncamera.com) using the promotional pricing provided for the Contest. Display prints ordered through Downtown Camera are picked up weekly by SCB-TO and do not need to be mailed to SCB-TO. Display prints obtained from any other photographic printing establishments may be mailed to: Society for Conservation Biology - Toronto Chapter, c/o Dept. of Ecology and Evolutionary Biology, University of Toronto, Room 417, 25 Harbord Street, Toronto, Ontario, M5S 3G5. No other attempted method of entry will be accepted or acknowledged. Automated entries are prohibited, and any use of such automated devices will cause disqualification. All entrants must have a valid e-mail address to enter. 
        %li 
          %strong Contest entry restrictions: 
          Limit five (5) photograph submissions per person. Entries indicating the same contact information (name, email, telephone, etc.) will be considered, for the purpose of the Contest to belong to the same Participant and are therefore subject to the above restriction. Excess Entries SCB-TO reasonably believes belong to the same Participant will be considered invalid.
        %ol{ type: 'a' }
          %li All Entries should be related to the appreciation of nature and wildlife and in line with SCB-TO’s mission of advancing the science and practice of conserving the Earth's biological diversity. Photo(s), related content and comments must not contain or encourage any illegal acts, nor contain any obscene, defamatory, threatening, pornographic, harassing, hateful, racially or ethnically offensive content. 
          %li Photo(s) must be true to life, only adjustments to the overall image which preserve the integrity of the photograph are permitted.

