          Participants selected as winners will be contacted by phone or e-mail (using the contact information provided by Participant at time of entering the Contest) at least three (3) times within the seven (7) days after the announcement of the winners. If the selected Participant cannot be contacted in that time, the Participant with next highest ranked Entry will be selected and the initial selected Participant will be disqualified and will have no recourse towards SCB-TO or anyone involved in the Contest. Prizes must be picked up in person, by the participant with valid photo identification, at the Award Ceremony held on May 30, 2014. Should the Participant be unable to attend the Award Ceremony, pick up must be arranged with the Contest organizing committee within fourteen (14) days of the Awards Ceremony or the Participant forfeits the prize. Prizes will not be mailed. Participants will be required to sign a Declaration and Release Form confirming compliance with the Contest Rules, acceptance of the Prize as awarded and releasing SCB-TO from all liability relating to the Contest. Selected Participants must also provide model releases and signatures for any individuals in the photo(s). No substitution for, replacement or transfer of the Prize, will be allowed.
